Platforms Comparison Overview

- Tested 7 different AI development platforms over 3.5 hours
- Built the same side hustle directory application on each platform
- Primary features tested: Basic CRUD, authentication, database integration
- Average build time per platform: ~30 minutes
- Total cost across all platforms: Under $5

Top Performing Platforms

Replit

- Most transparent pricing model
- Clear distinction between AI agent ($0.05/checkpoint) and assistant modes
- Successful Firebase integration
- Current spend: $2.79 (resets in 5 days)
- Main limitation: URL authentication issues with Firebase

Bolt + Supabase

- Strong design capabilities
- Intuitive interface
- Some Supabase connection errors but resolved after generation
- Pricing model less transparent than Replit
- Good for non-technical users

**Marblism**

- Most sophisticated development environment
- Includes VS Code editor integration
- New no-code editor addition
- Best modern design out of box
- Target audience: Technical users
- Main competitor challenge: Why use over GitHub Copilot

Emerging Platforms

**Lovable**

- Fast-moving development team
- Active Twitter presence
- Frequent feature updates
- Current limitation: Multiple Supabase integration errors
- Good documentation and prompting handbook

**Data Button**

- Clean interface
- Firebase integration attempts failed
- Deployment issues after initial build
- Good color schemes and UI
- Need to refresh often to resolve errors

### Basic/Experimental Platforms

**Grok Labs**

- Very basic functionality
- Quick deployment
- Good for testing simple ideas
- Limited features but novel approach
- Useful for rapid prototyping

**Lazy AI**

- Basic SQLite + Flask + Peewee stack
- Simple pricing: Free tier with daily limits
- Pro tier: $19/month or $400/year (50% discount)
- Limited design capabilities
- Fast build time but basic features
- Deployment requires $30/month tier

title: Native App vs PWA What is the DIFFERENCE? | No Code App builder Words
description:
Native app vs web app?  What's the difference?  Today I'm breaking down what a native app is, what a web app (or PWA) is, and which one YOU should use for your new app!

If you want to compare more no code builder apps, check out the full playlist: https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLfLZisr0-a4Q8oihMM_gB6d7Oecz1jGVu

More details:
Native apps are made for a mobile device and downloaded on the device. 
For example, making apps in Xcode for iOS devices.
For android coding with Java to create apps.

A PWA or web app is an optimized website meant for mobile.
Just like a website can be made with tons of different types of code, the same is true with a PWA. And just like a website builder like Squarespace, Wix etc. No code or visual programming platforms can be used for a PWA. For example, Bubble (a visual programming platform) or Softr which is a no code platform.

To check Bubble- https://bubble.io/
Softr- https://www.softr.io/?via=doc

Things to consider: Needing a team to execute a full plan and also to prevent burnout.

- Campaigns to promote the event, coordination for speakers and the event day, sponsorships for the brand (tiers of sponsors)

3) Thought Leader- Purpose or Mission that you can rally behind. This is impacting your industry and disrupting the status quo.

description:
Brief description: This episode we review Brand Factory Inc. entire content creation and how we create 15+ pieces of content with only 15 mins of work.

Sign Up for our Next Live Build Here- https://hi.switchy.io/1P9Y

Who this is for Content Creators and Brands

Basic Skills Needed: Fullstack Devs. Intermediate

GaryVee Content Model 2.0
https://youtu.be/k2UnFk37FNo

Tools mentioned in the video:
Ecamm Live 
Restream.io
Notion
Repurpose.io Remix for micro Content
Social Animal
Match Maker 
ConvertKit- CRM
IFTTT

Automation
Ecamm Live- Broadcasting and integration with Restream 
IFTTT- New Youtube video posted on Twitter
Restream- Notifications going live, transcriptions
Repurpose- Cuing videos + Quotes, scheduling micro-content

The Process

Record Pillar content- Build with Me (Authority)

Details: Record pillar content via Ecamm Live sending it to ReStream

-Pillar content with at least two 1) Intro-clip after approx. 3 minutes of intro music. Intro to episode becoming a teaser trailer of an episode for social media with CTA for the complete episode, 2) Recap at the End of the Pillar Content. (Time for it found in Notes for show)

FB- transcription + Marking to Team in Notion
- Note: If you have a video under 10 minutes you don't need to cut anything out (for IGTV or LinkedIn)

Automation for Pillar Content

Restream notifies Facebook, Twitter when the host is live on Twitch and Youtube. (2)

When a video is uploaded, video is shared on Twitter (IFTTT) (1)

**Micro Content**

Content is put out on [Repurpose.io](http://repurpose.io) and put in the queue to publish. The content can be scheduled for specific days to be sent out as well.

**Automation in place**

1) A podcast to LinkedIn (Business Page + reshare to personal) (2)

1.5- Video to Podcast for podcast show (1)

2) LinkedIn clips (Intro) Repurpose (2-5) Intro + Wrap-up

3) FB Live Video cued for IGTV (1)

4) Create a blog about pillar content with a link to a video of pillar content, picture and possible quotes for the show. The blog should have 5-10 links and an H1 and H2 tag.

When a story becomes a blog post you can send content out as an RSS Feed that will generate an email in ConvertKit and can send a list of PR reps a sample of the article to the Press.

To write the blog, you can use the words from the recap at the end of every Build with Me video.

For full transcription, you can send it Temi.

Blog Post + Email (2)

StoryChief (Google My Business, Medium, Ambassadors and Press Releases)

Quu Promote (5-15)

Manual: Check Social Animal to share and tag influencers on social Twitter and other platforms.

Step 1: 3:21 Sign into Zoom account

Step 3: 4:19 Log into Restream.io

Step 5: 5:31 Configure live streaming settings by adding stream URL, stream key, and live streaming URL.
Step 6: 6:59 Add channel to stream to. Add Channels in Restream.io
Step 7: 7:31 Go back to Zoom and Start Meeting in Zoom
Step 8: 7:43 During the live meeting in Zoom click the more icon and click 'Live on Custom Live Streaming Service'

Comment below and let us know if you have any questions.


This is How to stream a zoom call to Facebook, youtube and more,


Question for Ask Doc
Question: I use zoom to record interviews. Got a way to share that to other platforms?
And to keep the chat in a single place?

Answer: You can live stream zoom to a custom service by using a custom RTMP in zoom and connecting it to Restream. From Restream it can push it live up to 3-10 other platforms live depending on your plan.

Zoom https://zoom.us/

Zoom Client for Windows or Mac version 4.0.x
